org.jmisb.api.klv.st0903.vtrack

Class VTrackItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jmisb.api.klv.st0903.vtrack.VTrackItem
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IKlvValue, INestedKlvValue

    public class VTrackItem
extends Object
implements IKlvValue, INestedKlvValue
    VMTI Target Pack.

    The target pack represents a single VMTI target. It consists of a target id (integer value, always required) and a set of variable values that can be considered as attributes of the target.

      • VTrackItem

        public VTrackItem(byte[] bytes,
                  int offset,
                  int length,
                  EncodingMode encodingMode)
           throws KlvParseException
        Construct from encoded bytes.

        This is used to parse out a single VTargetPack from the KLV-encoded byte array.

        This constructor allows selection of which encoding rules (according to the ST0903 version) to apply for floating point data.

        Parameters:
        bytes - the byte array
        offset - the offset into the bytes array to start parsing.
        length - the number of bytes to parse
        encodingMode - which encoding mode the bytes parameter uses for floating point data
        Throws:
        KlvParseException - if there is a problem during parsing
